00:27:01.530 --> 00:27:03.420
about 25-calories in a marshmallow.
So, putting those things together, I could

00:27:03.420 --> 00:27:11.180
say that there's about 75-calories for every
cubic inch of marshmallow.

00:27:11.180 --> 00:27:22.810
Now, looking at Mr. Stay Puft, he's about
the size of a ten-story building.

00:27:22.810 --> 00:27:33.520
Each story of the building is going to be
about 14 feet.

00:27:33.520 --> 00:27:36.530
Therefore he's going to be about 140 feet
tall.

00:27:36.530 --> 00:27:48.040
He's going to be a little less than half of
that amount wide.

00:27:48.040 --> 00:27:57.380
So we'll say 60 feet wide.
We'll say 60 feet deep.

00:27:57.380 --> 00:28:12.340
And from that, I just multiply all those numbers
together.

00:28:12.340 --> 00:28:30.720
I get his total volume, which will be on the
order of 500,000 cubic feet.

00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:36.320
And I can also convert that to inches.
So then the last part is, like we said before,

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:42.240
just cancel the units, multiply "calories
per inches cubed" by "inches cubed," you get

00:28:42.240 --> 00:28:47.700
the number of calories, about 64 billion calories.
Now, if you take the FDA recommended 2000

00:28:47.700 --> 00:28:51.670
calories per day, now we can calculate it
would take about 80,000 years to eat it.

00:28:51.670 --> 00:28:59.310
So this is a pretty fun example, I hope.
